What is an Ansible Playbook?
    A playbook is a YAML file that tells Ansible:
    
    Which hosts to run on
    
    Which user to connect as
    
    What tasks to execute
    
    Whether sudo is required
    
    Think of it as instructions written in steps, executed over SSH.- name: Play description
  


Basic Structure
  hosts: target_group
  become: yes
  tasks:
    - name: Task description
      module_name:
        option: value
